// A procedure can return a value: `returns { r : ty }` names the result binder
// its `ensures` constrains, the body assigns it, and a call binds the result at
// an assignment. The caller still reasons from the contract alone.
procedure max (a, b) returns { r : int } =
  requires { true }
  ensures { r >= a && r >= b && (r = a || r = b) }
  writes { }
  if a >= b then r := a else r := b end
end

{ true }
m := max(3, 7)
{ m = 7 }
